title: kobayashi_makoto_(illustrator)
body:
Illustrator, Sci-Fi mecha designer, mangaka and animation director. The author of [[Dragon's Heaven]] and [[HYPERWEAPON]] series.
He is best known as the designer of [[Baund Doc]] and [[The O (mobile Suit)|]] from [[Zeta Gundam]].

[[Japan]]ese name: [b]小林 誠[/b] ([i]Kobayashi Makoto[/i])

title: nexas_(vtuber)
body:
A defunct [[virtual YouTuber|VTuber]] agency whose talents all streamed on the streaming app [[AniLive]] that aimed to be an "academia" for talents aspiring to be the next generation of virtual stars. Later, most talents would start streaming on YouTube and/or Twitch, either stopping activities on AniLive completely, do streams on both AniLive and their platform that they stream on or do a mix of both AniLive and YouTube or Twitch (depending on what platform the talent debuted on) streams in a week based on their schedule. The company was founded by forCreators CEO Harry So, who is depicted as an [[owl]].

NEXAS completed angel funding in December 2023, launched in February 2024 and began operations in April of the same year. On December 9, 2024, NEXAS announced that it would cease operations as a talent agency on January 31, 2025, with talents getting the opportunity to keep their models and become [[indie virtual youtuber|independent]], instead becoming a hub to connect content creators with opportunities. On the day of its closure, it announced that "Phase 1" (the VTuber agency phase) had been completed, but they said that it wasn't over for them and that "Phase 2" would start later in 2025.

At the time of closure, it managed 61 members (24 in Class Genesis, 13 in Class Nebulink, 8 in Class Yume and 16 in Class Tensei). There were also 6 other members that have either graduated or gotten fired.

Not to be confused with the [[nexas|artist of the same name]].

title: echidna_(fate)
body:
Character introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Atlantis (fate/grand order)|]] Lostbelt. She is considered the "mother of monsters" in Greek mythology, and is used in the Lostbelt to mass-produce monsters for [[Odysseus (fate)|]]'s army. As she is the granddaughter of [[Medusa (fate)|]], [[Medusa (Saber) (fate)|]] can manifest her when using her [[Noble Phantasm (fate)|]].

title: dianzi
body:
Traditional Chinese hat of the [[Manchu clothes|Manchurian people]].

It's semicircular in shape, reminiscent of a [[kepi]] or [[newsboy cap]], with its visor. However, some versions do not have a visor. Its literal translation is [i]hat ring[/i]. 

It's often a made up of a metal frame, adorned with materials like silk or rattan. Common patterns on the dianzi includes dragons, phoenixes, butterflies, bats, flowers and clouds. 

It was often worn over [[liangbatou]], to protect the hairstyle. It is hat, so tiara shaped hair ornaments/hairbands may be better described as [[dalachi (headdress)|]] or [[fengguan]].

h4. Examples

* !post #7796708
* !post #7220180: Dianzi with [[lappet]]s (hat flaps)

h4. See also

* [[Dalachi (headdress)|]]
* [[Fengguan]]
* [[Kokoshnik]]
* [[Zhuang hat]]

* "Westca forums (Photo examples of the dianzi)":[https://www.westca.com/pda/forums/op=view_next/t=1182713/lang=schinese.html#0]

title: newsboy_cap
body:
Also known as a "cabbie cap" or "cabbie hat".

It has a stiff [[visor]] in front and a band. The body of the hat is roundish and puffy. Not to be confused with [[beret]]s, which are often flat or floppy with the band under its body and no visor. It has a similar shape to a [[flat cap]], but the body of the cap is rounder, made of eight pieces, fuller, and paneled with a button on top.

title: luke_triton
body:
A primary character from the [i][[Professor Layton]][/i] series. 
[[Hershel Layton]]'s boy assistant, and the son of Layton's longtime friend Clark Triton. He is able to communicate with animals in addition to his sharp intuition.

Luke has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and [[black eyes]]. He usually wears a [[blue headwear|blue]] [[newsboy cap]], a [[blue sweater]] with [[long sleeves]] and a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] underneath, [[suspenders hanging|hanging]] [[suspenders]], [[green shorts]], [[white socks]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]]. He also carries a [[brown bag|brown]] [[shoulder bag]].

He later appears in [i][[Layton's Mystery Journey]][/i] as an adult, married and a seasoned adventurer.

title: miyako_yoshika
body:
The "Loyal Undead". Stage 3 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Ten Desires]]. A [[jiangshi]], or Chinese zombie, with the ability to eat anything. Humans bitten by her may turn into a jiangshi temporarily. Assigned to guard the cemetery adjacent to the [[Myouren Temple]] by [[Kaku Seiga]], she's a tough opponent who takes her duties seriously but is somewhat dumb. Referred to as a "meaningless bodyguard" by ZUN. She is partially based on Miyako No Yoshika, a real 9th century poet who was rumored to be friends with [[Ibaraki Douji (touhou)|]].

h4. Appearance 
* !asset #23118598
Both her hair and eye color are inconsistently drawn, [[blue eyes|with]] [[black eyes|either]] [[purple eyes|being]] [[blue hair|blue]], [[black hair|black]], or [[purple hair|purple]]. She wears a [[purple hat|purple]] [[newsboy cap]] with a [[star hat ornament|star]], an [[ofuda]] on her forehead, a [[black ribbon|black]] [[neck ribbon]], a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[red shirt|red]] [[tangzhuang]] with [[lace-trimmed sleeves|a lace trim on the sleeves]], a [[black skirt]] sometimes with a [[floral print|floral]] [[print skirt|print]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

h4. See also

* [[Miyako Yoshika (living)]]
* [[List of Touhou Characters]]
* [[Zombie pose]]

title: shameimaru_aya
body:
The "Traditional Reporter of Fantasy". First appeared as an opponent (and later, playable character) in the ninth [[Touhou]] game, [i][[Phantasmagoria of Flower View]][/i]. She has since reappeared in other games as a playable character, and often appears in the various print works.

Aya is a crow tengu, and has the ability to manipulate the wind in addition to the exceptional sight and long-range hearing possessed by most tengu. She is also absurdly fast, perhaps even the fastest in Gensokyo. She runs, reports, and photographs for her own newspaper, the [i][[Bunbunmaru]] Shinbun[/i]. However, the publication is notorious for being filled with rumors, gossip, and personal opinion. 

She is the rival of fellow journalist [[Himekaidou Hatate]], who runs the [i]Kakashi Nenpo[/i] ("Kakashi Spirit Times"). She was (and still is) also often depicted in fanworks as a friend to (or the superior of) the white wolf tengu [[Inubashiri Momiji]], one of the guardians of Youkai Mountain. However, it was revealed in [[Double Spoiler]] that the two actually dislike one another. 

Her catchphrase is "[[ayaya~]]".

h4. Appearance 
Aya has [[red eyes]] and [[black hair]] of varying lengths. Her outfits have changed somewhat throughout her various appearances, but by far her most common outfit is a small [[red hat|red]] [[tokin hat]] with two strings of [[pom_pom_(clothes)|pom poms]] attached, a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] with a [[black ribbon]] tied around the collar, [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[black skirt]], [[black socks|black]] [[kneehighs|knee-high socks]], and [[red footwear|red]] [[tengu-geta]]. She often carries around an old [[camera]], a [[notebook]] and [[calligraphy brush]], and a [[hauchiwa]] (a leaf-shaped fan).

Due to variations in depiction, she may also have [[pointy ears]] or long, [[black wings|black]] [[bird wings|feathered wings]]. Her outfit may also sport an [[armband]] or a tan, [[leaf print|leaf-patterned stripe]] motif. Other times, she may be shown wearing a completely different outfit, such as the [[Kourindou Tengu costume]] from [[Curiosities of Lotus Asia|CoLA]] or her combination of a [[newsboy cap]], [[necktie|tie]], and [[suit jacket]] from [[Forbidden Scrollery]] which should be tagged as [[Shameimaru Aya (newsboy)]].

h4. See also

* [[ayaya~]]
* [[kimeemaru]]

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Aya Shameimaru":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Aya_Shameimaru

title: kyrie_canaan
body:
Kyrie Canaan is a minor character in [[Final Fantasy VII Remake]], and the female protagonist in The Kids Are Alright: A Turks Side Story. She is a former delinquent from Midgar's Sector 5 Slums who later serves as a detective alongside her boyfriend, Evan Townshend.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] with [[bangs]] and [[brown eyes]], and wears a [[black headwear|black]] [[newsboy cap]] and a [[cropped_vest|cropped]] [[double-breasted]] [[grey vest]] with an [[undershirt]] and [[denim shorts]] with [[black shorts|black]] [[bike shorts]] underneath.  She wears [[striped thighhighs]] with [[black footwear|black]] [[lace-up boots|lace-up]] [[knee boots]] and a pare of [[brown gloves]].

title: shirogane_naoto
body:
One of the main characters of [[Persona 4]]. An accomplished detective.

Naoto is [[androgynous]] in appearance, with [[short hair|short]] [[blue hair]] and [[grey eyes]] ([[blue eyes|blue]] in The Animation and Arena). She wears [[yasogami school uniform|Yasogami High's]] [[gakuran]]. Naoto is often seen wearing formal clothing such as blue shirts, ties, and her trademark blue [[newsboy cap|cap]]. She [[reverse trap|crossdresses]] to hide her true gender and her [[large breasts]].

Her Persona are [[Sukuna-Hikona (Persona 4)|]], [[Yamato Takeru (Persona)|]] and Yamato Sumeragi of The Fortune arcana.

Voiced by: [[Paku Romi]] (Japanese), Anna Graves (English, PS2 release, [[Persona 4 The Golden|Golden]], [[Persona 4: The Ultimate in Mayonaka Arena|Arena]]), [[Mary Elizabeth McGlynn]] (English, [[Persona 4 The Animation|The Animation]]), Valerie Arem (English, all other appearances)

title: foreign_disciples_(fate/grand_order)
body:
Major antagonists in the second arc of [[Fate/Grand Order]], seven servants summoned by the Alien God, [[U-Olga Marie]], to assist the [[Crypters (fate/grand order)|]] in replacing greater human history with that of the Lostbelts. [spoiler]It turns out that unbeknownst to her, U-Olga Marie is also one of the disciples rather than the mastermind.[/spoiler] This tag applies if [b]at least 3[/b] are present in an image.

The disciples include:
* The God, [[U-Olga Marie]]. [spoiler]Manifested by mistake but repurposed to serve as the overseer for the other disciples. Initially believed to the Alien God itself.[/spoiler]
* The Priest, [[Grigori rasputin (fate)|]]. [spoiler]Summoned to surveil the Crypters.[/spoiler]
* The Malignant Incarnation, [[Ashiya Douman (fate)|]]. [spoiler]Summoned to surveil the Lostbelt Kings and make sure none of the Lostbelts would overtake the [[Olympus (fate/grand order)|Greek Lostbelt]].[/spoiler]
* The Atlas Slayer, [spoiler][[Senji Muramasa (fate)|]]. Summoned to prevent [[Kirschtaria Wodime]]'s plot to destroy the Alien God.[/spoiler]
* The Detective, [spoiler][[Sherlock Holmes (fate)|]]. Summoned to help Chaldea defeat [[Goetia (fate)|]] and the first 6 Lostbelts. Had his memories wiped and defected to Chaldea.[/spoiler]
* The Professor, [spoiler][[James Moriarty (Ruler) (fate)|]]. Summoned to kill the traitor [[Sherlock Holmes (fate)|]] and then take control of Chaldea.[/spoiler]
* The Count, [spoiler][[Alessandro di Cagliostro (fate)|]]. Summoned to observe Chaldea.[/spoiler]
[[Koyanskaya (fate)|]] was initially believed by Novum Chaldea to be one of the disciples before being revealed to be an independent party working alongside them. For tagging purposes she may be included in the count.

h4. See Also
* [[Crypters (fate/grand order)|]]

title: johanna-san_to_mikakunin_no_ai
body:
[b]Johanna and the Unidentified Love: Smash 'em Up☆Love, Lovers, and the Great Stone Statue[/b]
[quote]Valentine's Day. The day of love is a busy one, not just for those who devote themselves to making homemade chocolates, but also for those who pray over the chocolates! Pope Johanna is no exception.

"May this chocolate find joy, however humble."

An alarm announcing the appearance of the yearly minute Singularity cuts through the serenity of prayer. Although the Holy Grail at the Rayshift destination is easily found, Johanna inadvertently touches it...

...and the next thing everyone knows, they find themselves in an unfamiliar forest and discover a giant statue. Get ready for the heartwarming(?) story set to unfold this year![/quote]

A limited time [[Valentine]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on February 17, 2023 and on the NA server on February 7, 2025.

title: fate/accel_zero_order
body:
[b]The Fourth Revelation: Fuyuki[br]Fate/Accel Zero Order[/b]
[quote]Japan, Fuyuki—
A new singularity has appeared on the site of Singularity F,
but at coordinates ten years prior.
The timeline sees a Fuyuki embroiled in the Fourth Holy Grail War.
Your guide for this Rayshift will be Lord El-Melloi II.
What has happened to the Fourth Holy Grail War?
A battle to discover the truth is about to begin...
[/quote]

A collaboration event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] with [[Fate/Zero]] guest written by [[Urobuchi Gen]], released on the Japanese server on April 27, 2016 and on the NA server on April 19, 2018. The story is a retelling of the events of Fate/Zero with interference from Chaldea and [[Lord El-Melloi II]]. title: halloween_rising!
body:
[b]Desert Fairy Tale Ritual: Csejte Cinderella[br]Halloween Rising! ~The Queen of Dust and the Disciple of Darkness~[/b]
[quote]Trick or Torture!

Attention my little pumpkins around the world! The Halloween season—MY season—is here again! At least that's what I want to say, but this year's Halloween stage is a bit...strange. My dress is in shambles, but I act elegantly when the opportunity arises, and I'm also arrogant(?) at times. And it looks like this Singularity is set in a absurd fairy tale world...

Well obviously there's only one thing this perfect Cinderella needs to do! A Cinderella needs a castle! And a castle needs the ultimate prince! Now that that's settled, I need to go out there to win back my Cinderella (Csejte) castle! I'm looking forward to having you escort me, Master♥[/quote]

A limited time [[Halloween]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on October 20, 2021 and on the NA server on October 11, 2023. [[Elizabeth Bathory (Cinderella) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: servant_summer_camp!
body:
[b]Chilling Dreamlike Nether Peak: Paradise Lake[br]Servant Summer Camp! ~Chaldea's Thriller Night~[/b]
[quote]A new Singularity has been detected in Japan. Is this the work of someone with a devious plan, or is it a product of the usual summer shenanigans? With many questions unanswered, the team Rayshifts to a lake in the mountains.

That's right: this summer isn't confined to a beach! Barbecuing, boating, fishing...all manner of mountain and lakeside recreation awaits to help you forget the hustle and bustle of city life! The Servant Summer Camp... is now open!

But...be careful at night. After all, ghost stories, haunted trails, and strange, surreal happenings are just some of the phenomena in the mountains during a summer night![/quote]

A limited time [[Summer]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on August 17, 2020 and on the NA server on July 12, 2022. [[Yu Mei-ren (Swimsuit Lancer) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: saber_wars_ii
body:
[b]Shining Blue Galactic Space Opera: Saber Wars 4.8[br]SABER WARS 2 ~To the Beginning of Space~[/b]
[quote]This story has absolutely nothing to do with the main story...
In fact, it may have happened, and it may not have.
It is much like a certain blockbuster film franchise we all know so well.

In an unexpected turn of events, you have been taken to space. You panic at first, but your usual conviction that things will work out eventually kicks in, and you just hurl yourself into the final frontier. The Shining Blue Galaxy, also known as the Servant Universe, awaits you, brimming with both chaos and the myriad desires of its people.
Get your space suit on and embark on an unprecedented adventure![/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on October 30, 2019 and on the NA server on October 18, 2021.

title: devil_fruit
body:
A mysterious fruit that grants superpowers at the expense of the ability to swim in the world of [[One Piece]]. They come in three basic types, are typically covered in swirly lines and they all taste awful.

Their powers are unique and only one user of the same power exists at the same time. Eating more than one fruit is considered fatal, thus no one can have more than one power (the only exception being [[Marshall D. Teach]] for some unknown reason) The fruits "respawn" in a regular fruit after the user dies.

[b]Logia Type:[/b]
Elemental type, allows the user to turn into and control a certain "element" such as Fire, Smoke or Mud.

[b]Zoan Type:[/b]
Animal type, allows the user to transform into a certain animal (including humans) as well as intermediate forms. Also exists in Ancient- (extinct) and Mythological types. Can have additional powers depending on the animal type.

[[Dr. Vegapunk]]'s research has created a method to "feed" zoan type fruits to in-animate objects as well as a method to create artificial zoan fruits.

[b]Paramecia Type:[/b]
The most varied form of devil fruit, as all powers that don't fit into the above types are considered paramecia.

title: shikomizue
body:
The [b]shikomizue[/b], [b]shikomi-zue[/b] (仕込み杖, [i]"prepared cane"[/i]) or [b]jotou[/b] (杖刀, [i]"staff sword"[/i]) is a Japanese [[sword]] [[stick]] or [[concealed weapon]]. 

It is most famous for its use by the fictional swordmaster [[Zatoichi]]. The sword blade was placed in a cane-like mounting ([i]tsue[/i]) as concealment.

Some shikomi-zue also concealed metsubushi, chains, hooks, and many other things. Shikomi-zue could be carried in public without arousing suspicion, making them perfect tools for [[ninja]].

Typically, Doodle sensei is depicted literally as a doodle from head to toe. title: o_medal
body:
A general term referring to the transformation items used in [[Kamen Rider OOO (series)|]]. The components that make up a Greeed and as a representation of desire and greed, O medals are classified in two categories: Core Medal and [[Cell Medal]].

Core Medals are what makes up a Greeed and comes in three types: Head, Body, and Legs. These medals are what Hino Eiji uses to transform into [[Kamen Rider OOO]].

Cell Medals are the manifestation of human desire and make up the body of a Greeed and Yummy. These are used for the technology developed by the Kougami Foundation as well as the transformation item used by [[Kamen Rider Birth]]. 

For another explanation, the character Ankh explains that the medals are like a popsicle in the sense that Cells are what makes the ice cream part of a popsicle and Cores are the stick to keep it together.

title: official_alternate_color
body:
[[Alternate color]]s of official origin. This tag should be used when a significant amount of a character's color palette is different; if only a specific part of a character is a different color, use a different tag instead (for example, if only the hair color is different, use [[official alternate hair color]]).

Characters or beings may change colors to represent an alternate idea for the character, which could include an [[alternate form]]. This can be encountered in different forms such as a skin for a character in a video game or during a character's special action.

[b]Do not[/b] use this tag with [[alternate color]], the tags are mutually exclusive.

h4. Examples

* [[Acheron (honkai: star rail)|]] from [[Honkai: Star Rail]] has her outfit, hair, eyes and leg tattoo change colour during her ultimate attack.
* [[Mega Man (character)|]], as well as many other characters from the [[Mega Man (series)|]] series, changes colors depending of the weapon he has equipped.
* [[Pyra (xenoblade)|]] from [[Xenoblade Chronicles 2]] has an alternate dark color [[Super Smash Bros.]] skin.

title: tenshi_kaiwai
body:
Tenshi Kaiwai (lit. "angel neighborhood") or Mizuiro (lit. "water-colored") is a Japanese aesthetic and fashion style defined by the combination of light blue and white. It heavily incorporates imagery of [[angel]]s, [[water]], [[cloud]]s, [[pill]]s and [[syringe]]s, and technology.

Fashion tends to include [[track jacket]]s and [[jersey maid]] outfits, as well as [[arm warmers]] and [[leg warmers]], to the point that Tenshi Kaiwai and jersey maids are sometimes conflated. Fashion is not limited to jersey-type streetwear, however, and may incorporate a variety of other inspirations.

title: smith_&_wesson_m1917
body:
The [[Smith & Wesson]] version of the M1917 [[revolver]], manufactured to supplement the [[M1911]] in the United States Military during [[World War I]]. It is a six-shot, double-action revolver designed to fire .45 ACP, and later, .45 Auto Rim cartridges. 

Though both are designated M1917, the Colt and Smith & Wesson versions have subtle differences, such as the Colt requiring moon clips due to its lack of a shoulder in the cylinder for the cartridges to headspace on. The Smith & Wesson version does have this shoulder, so moon clips aren't required, though an extraction rod is required to remove the spent shell casings if moon clips are not utilized.

title: desert
body:
An arid, barren environment. Usually covered in predominantly [[sand]] or very loose soil with few animals and plants (e.g. [[palm tree]]s and [[cactus|cacti]]) which can survive with very small amounts of water.

Commonly featured in Middle Eastern setting or [[post-apocalypse]] fiction to show that resources are scarce or some event has killed most of the life on Earth.

[b]Not to be confused[/b] with sweet food items consumed at the end of a meal, known as a [[dessert]].

title: zeta_(granblue_fantasy)
body:
Character in [i][[Granblue Fantasy]][/i].

A spirited female knight wielding the mythic Spear of Arvess. She is a member of the shadowy group known as The Society alongside [[beatrix_(granblue_fantasy)|Beatrix]], [[eustace_(granblue_fantasy)|Eustace]], and [[vaseraga|Vaseraga]]. She wants the protagonist, who she acknowledges as a powerful, primal beast slaying warrior, to join The Society and decided to wait for their answer, joining their crew in the meantime. Eyes glittering sharp and blue, she proves her strength by pursuing only the most dangerous of prey. No wall nor enemy can stand up to her steely will and burning spear. Although her form may be fair, her words bite deeper than the tip of her spear sharp words are the mark of a hardened warrior.

title: magnum_research_bfr
body:

The BFR is available in a myriad of different [[handgun cartridge|pistol]] and [[rifle cartridge|rifle calibers]], and can be custom-ordered in various barrel lengths. Short and long cylinder versions are also available, depending on caliber.

Officially, "BFR" stands for "Biggest, Finest Revolver", though many colloquially refer to it as "Big Fucking Revolver."

title: bridal_gauntlets

[b]Note[/b]: This tag refers to a specific style of glove and [b]does not[/b] refer to every glove worn with a [[wedding dress]]. Gloves worn with a wedding dress that are not of this specific style should simply be tagged [[wedding dress]] and [[gloves]] instead.

title: the_vvitch
body:
The Witch (stylized as The VVitch, and subtitled A New-England Folktale) is a 2015 folk horror film written and directed by Robert Eggers in his feature directorial debut. It stars Anya Taylor-Joy in her feature film debut, alongside Ralph Ineson, Kate Dickie, Harvey Scrimshaw, Ellie Grainger, and Lucas Dawson. Set in 1630s New England, the narrative follows a Puritan family who are preyed upon by an evil force in the woods beyond their farm. In fear and desperation, they turn upon one another.

body:

title: le_cygne
body:
A fictional giant manned robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in the spin-off [[Zeta Gundam]] manga [[Ecole du Ciel]]. 

[b]MSS-008 Le Cygne[/b] 

A Newtype-use, Gundam-type [[mobile suit]] that is designed for [[Asuna Elmarit]]'s use. 

Unlike several mobile suits during the Gryps Conflict, the Le Cygne doesn't transform and it is armed with some experimental equipment, such as a large, physical [[shield]] with several [[thrusters]] that adds onto the Gundam's speed and mobility, which also enables the shield to be used as a very effective ramming weapon, and a type of [[double-blade|double-bladed]] [[beam saber]] that is called a [i]Twin Beam Trident[/i] (the beam emitter on each end can generate 3 beam blades: one with a standard length in the middle and 2 shorter ones at the sides. Hence, its name). 

Its design is also unusual for a UC-era Gundam-type mobile suit. Its real life designer, [[Sayama Yoshinori]] stated that he created the Le Cygne's design with a [[ninja|kunoichi]] motif and also removed a number of standard Gundam traits onto it (ex. having a forward extending shoulder armor instead of standard sideward extending ones)

title: gaplant_custom_erisia_special
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in the [[Zeta Gundam]] spin-off manga [[Ecole du Ciel]] from 2001.

A variation of the transforming [[mobile suit]] [[Gaplant]], it has a head unit that is equipped with enhanced communication sensors which were feather-like in arrangement, and the entire machine had been painted pink and purple along with ornate markings. The Gaplant Custom Erisia Special featured improved movable shield binders with increased firepower in the form of a right arm binder with built-in twin [[beam cannon|beam cannons]] and [[thrusters]], and a left arm binder fitted with a large [[shield]] that incorporated [[vernier thrusters]] for defensive purposes. An interesting design feature of this MS is the machine cannon and [[gatling gun]] built into the waist section, which would become a bow-mounted weapon in its [[mobile armor]] mode.

As said in its name, its pilot is [[Erisia Nocton]].

title: erisia_nocton
body:
A fictional female character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. She first appeared in the [[Zeta Gundam]] spin-off manga [[Ecole du Ciel]] from 2001. 

She is the main rival of the manga's main protagonist, [[Asuna Elmarit]]. Like her rival, Erisia also piloted several [[mobile suit|mobile suits]], such as a [[Gaplant]], before settling down to its variant that became her signature MS, the [[Gaplant Custom Erisia Special]]. 

Erisia is also among of the franchise' earliest female [b][[Char Aznable|Char]] Clones[/b].

title: rozen_maiden
body:
A manga by the group [[PEACH-PIT]], with an anime series of the same name. It deals obliquely with the pressures placed on children in Japan by telling the story of a student, Jun Sakurada, who cracked under the strain. The series chronicles Jun's reluctant mental recovery through experiences with the Rozen Maiden, a series of enchanted dolls tasked with fighting each other and taking their life force known as the Rosa Mystica, in a process called the Alice Game.

title: gravity_daze
body:
(Shamelessly lifted directly from Wikipedia at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gravity_Rush)

[b]Gravity Rush[/b], known in Japan as [b]Gravity Daze[/b] (グラヴィティデイズ/重力的眩暈:上層への帰還において彼女の内宇宙に生じた摂動?) is a video game developed for the PlayStation Vita. Directed by Keiichiro Toyama and written by Naoko Sato (previously known for the Siren series and the first Silent Hill), the core mechanic of the game is the player's ability to manipulate gravity, allowing unique movements and navigation. The graphics are cel-shaded, which in Toyama's opinion stand out from the western photorealistic trend.

The game started off back in 2008 as a PlayStation 3 project called Gravité, before being eventually transferred to PS Vita. AI and visuals were slightly simplified during the process. However, Gravity Rush director thinks overall Vita suits the game better, because of "its handy and accessible nature" and "the impression of a different world existing beyond the screen" the player gets by tilting the device.

title: sinanju_stein
body:
A fictional combat manned robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

Ambiguous name, making reference to two different but very similar units: the [b]MSN-06S Sinanju Stein[/b], the prototype successor unit to the [[Nu Gundam]] developed by Anaheim Electronics, of which one was stolen and extensively modified into [[Full Frontal]]'s personal [[Sinanju]], and the [b]MSN-06S-2 Sinanju Stein[/b], a slightly cosmetically altered version of the prototype piloted by [[Zoltan Akkanen]].

title: revealing_chastity_cage
body:
A [[chastity cage]] design that lets you see the [[penis]] inside the chastity cage. Use this tag if

* A [[metal chastity cage]] is made of rings around the penis.
* A metal or plastic cage has an open frame or mesh.
* Small wires connect at the tip revealing the tip of the penis.
* A cage is made out of metal and leather straps that don't cover most of the penis.

If the penis is hidden by an enclosed tube, use [[tube chastity cage]] instead. If the tube is [[see-through]] use [[transparent chastity cage]] instead.

Do not use this tag if the only openings are breathing holes or the space between the ring and the tube.

This tag can be combined with [[tube chastity cage]] or [[nub chastity cage]] when the tip of the penis is revealed by wires.

h4. Correct examples

* Post #7345733 [tn]NSFW | Ringed chastity cage.[/tn]
* Post #3662299 [tn]NSFW | Wires connecting at the tip / birdcage type.[/tn]
* Post #3850868 [tn]NSFW | Metal frame.[/tn]
* Post #8259583 [tn]NSFW | Plastic frame / cobra type.[/tn]
* Post #8495414 [tn]NSFW | [[nub chastity cage]] with wires connecting at the tip.[/tn]
* Post #6856833 [tn]NSFW | [[tube chastity cage]] with wires connecting at the tip.[/tn]
* Post #1680043 [tn]NSFW | Leather straps and rings.[/tn]
* Post #5560597 [tn]NSFW | [[ornate chastity cage]].[/tn]


h4. Incorrect examples

* Post #8728271 [tn]NSFW | Just breathing holes.[/tn]
* Post #7546575 [tn]NSFW | Just space between tube and ring.[/tn]

title: transparent_chastity_cage
body:
A [[chastity cage]] made of glass-like resin or other [[see-through]] material that lets you see the [[penis]] inside the chastity cage.

If the material isn't transparent but there are large holes use [[revealing chastity cage]] instead.

title: colored_chastity_cage
body:
A [[chastity cage]] that has an [b]unusual[/b] color such as pink, red, green, blue or white.

Do NOT use this tag with black cages because most of them are black.

Do NOT use this tag with [[metal chastity cage]] and [[gold chastity cage]]. They have their own tags.

Use [[ornate chastity cage]] if the cage has multiple colors.

title: otouto_(92m)
body: The younger brother of [[Kinshi no Ane (92m)|Kinshi no Ane]]. Although his name is never revealed, for convenience we will refer to him with the Japanese word for "younger brother". He is frequently the viewpoint character in the [i]Near-Sighted Elder Sister[/i] series of illustrations (pool #17513) by [[92m]], and usually only his hands are visible; if he is depicted in a third-person view, it always used to be as a [[faceless male]] (i.e., with no eyes). However, his eyes started being drawn in post #7335492. His sister, her friend [[Dateko (92m)|]] and his classmate [[kakita (92m)|Kakita]] are rivals for his affections.

It is always held on March 17 each year, the recognized date of death for St. Patrick, and is associated with wearing [[green]] clothing and [[shamrock|shamrocks]], holding parades, and copious consumption of [[alcohol]].

title: sword_knot
body:
[b]Sword knots[/b] are decorative cords or straps that are attached to the hilt of a [[sword]]. They are used to help secure the sword to the wielder's wrist while in use, preventing the sword from being dropped or knocked out of the hand during combat. Sword knots are often made of braided [[leather]] or [[silk]] and can be intricately designed with [[tassel|tassels]], fringe, or other embellishments. 

In addition to their practical function, sword knots also serve a ceremonial or decorative purpose, adding a touch of elegance to the overall appearance of the sword.

h4. See Also
* [[Lanyard]]

title: trickcal
body:
An autochess-like 2D autobattler gacha game developed and published by Korean developer Epid Games. First starting life as an in-development dark fantasy chess-themed autobattler game titled [i]"Roll the Chess":https://youtu.be/8KJh2miy0ag[/i] in 2019, it would later be scrapped and have development restarted as [i]Trickcal[/i], a portmanteau of the words "trick" and "musical" according to the developer, with renowned Korean [[chibi]] artist [[Diyap]] joining the dev team as its main illustrator.

It would then officially release in Korea on September 27, 2021, but it was rife with launch issues so badly it would end up being set back to "open beta" status and then would later be pulled from service on October 3 in order to salvage what's left of the IP and restart development yet again. Diyap would later quit from Epid Games on January 19, 2022, and the developer would later find a new artist who could mimic his artstyle.

It would later relaunch as [i]Trickcal RE:VIVE[/i], parodying [[Cygames]]'s [[Princess Connect!]] Re:Dive, on September 27, 2023, 2 years after the initial launch. Despite setbacks and financial losses that could've ruined the developer a few months into the game's relaunch, "the CEO continued to invest in the game":https://www.khgames.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=235475, taking out loans when necessary, and ended up finding success within the casual playerbase after its first anniversary. The game is now preparing for a global release with additional Japanese voice acting, with its publishing partner seemingly being Chinese company [[Bilibili]] following a "Play Store leak":https://www.reddit.com/r/gachagaming/s/lwHlvhQFIa showing a test page for Trickcal's English server.

title: kantai_collection
body:
[i]Kantai Collection[/i] (艦隊これくしょん [i]Kantai Korekushon[/i], lit. "Combined Fleet Collection"), abbreviated as [i]KanColle[/i] (艦これ [i]KanKore[/i]), is a Japanese free-to-play shipgirl-themed game developed by [[c2_kikan]] under [[Kadokawa|Kadokawa Games]] and published by [[DMM]]. It is currently available exclusively in Japanese, though it has started to introduce some English-language graphical assets, and accessing the game for non-Japanese players requiring unconventional means.

h4. Gameplay

Gameplay is centered upon building squadrons composed of individual characters represented as cards with different attributes, and then sending said squadrons out on missions. The player takes on the role of an [[Admiral (kancolle)|]] (提督 [i]teitoku[/i]) and organises their fleets in battle in order to win. Combat is largely automated, and manual actions by the player include micromanagement such as building and repairing.

Each of the characters are moe [[personification]]s of [[World War II]] naval [[warship]]s, which are depicted as cute girls known as "ship girls" (艦娘, [i]kanmusu[/i]). These personified warships are based on real life vessels which are explained in detail within the game; the physical characteristics, appearances and personalities of each of the girls correlate in some way to the real life vessel.

Originally, the roster of the shipgirls was designed to be limited to the IJN and major players of the Imperial Japanese Army, and its final mission being an attack on the base, akin to how World War 2 played out for Japan. Due to the game's popularity, it has since introduced shipgirls from other Axis nations and wartime rival factions, including ships from the U.S. Navy, the British Royal Navy and even the somewhat-neutral Swedish Navy. 

As of early 2022, KanColle features ships from following navies: Imperial Japanese Navy, Imperial Japanese Army, Maritime Safety Agency/Japan Coast Guard, United States Navy, British Royal Navy, Royal Australian Navy, Dutch Koninklijke Marine, French Marine nationale, Italian Regia Marina, German Kriegsmarine, Военно-морской флот СССР, Swedish Svenska marinen, and Republic of China Navy. With the most numerous non-Japanese navies being United States Navy and Regia Marina.

h4. Media

The game has developed into a much larger media franchise; various media including multiple manga series and light novels have been released, in addition to an officially licensed [[tabletop rpg|tabletop role-playing game]]. A [[PlayStation Vita]] game was released February 2016. A [[Kantai Collection (anime)|television anime adaptation]] aired Winter 2015, with a sequel season airing in 2022, and an anime movie was released in 2016. There is also a Japan only 3D arcade game [[Kancolle Arcade]] that was released in 2016.

h4. History

The web browser game was launched on April 23, 2013, originally designed to run in Adobe Flash. An Android app version was released on August 1st, 2016. As of January 2015, the game had 2.5 million registered players. The game migrated to HTML5 prior to worldwide decommissioning of Adobe Flash in browsers.

h4. Tagging

Don't tag shipgirls with [[mecha musume]], [[personification]],  [[World War II]], or [[Imperial Japanese Navy]], unless these things are present outside of the shipgirls themselves.

Don't tag shipgirls of the same class as [[sisters]].

When in her [[idol clothes|PriPara form]], Non's hair [[very long hair|becomes much longer]]. Her main outfit consists of a [[pink hairband|pink]] [[frilled hairband|frilled]] [[lolita hairband]] decorated with a [[pink ribbon]] and a [[rabbit hair ornament|rabbit]], a [[sweet lolita]]  [[multicolored dress]] with [[puffy short sleeves]], a [[collared dress|collar]] and a lot of [[frilled dress|frills]], a [[pink bow]] in the neck area, [[center frills]], and a [[rabbit print]]. She wears [[wrist cuffs]] on her arms and [[white socks|white]] [[frilled socks]] as well as [[pink footwear|pink]] [[high heels|high heeled]] [[mary janes]] on her legs.
other_names: ノンシュガー(プリパラ)

title: bang_dream!
body:
Stylized as BanG Dream!, a Japanese media franchise created and managed by [[Bushiroad]]. 

Originally started as a mobile rhythm game, the franchise later expanded with an anime series being broadcast since January 2017, multiple mini anime series, several manga series, and live concerts in which the voice actresses for six of the bands ([[Poppin'Party]], [[Roselia (bang dream!)|]], [[RAISE A SUILEN]], [[Morfonica]], [[MyGO!!!!! (bang dream!)|]], and [[Ave Mujica (bang dream!)|]]) perform their instruments and respective roles.

In 2023, all of the main casts received a 3D live tracking model for their live and online performance, essentially making them pseudo-[[virtual youtuber]].

title: legal_high
body:
A Japanese TV Drama broadcast by Fuji TV between 2012/04/17 - 2012/06/26, The second season is currently aring since 2013/04/13.

Attorney [[Komikado Kensuke]] (Sakai Masato) loves money, prestige & women, but also has a 100% winning rate when it comes to his legal cases. [[Mayuzumi Machiko]] (Aragaki Yui) is a rookie attorney who holds a strong sense of justice; passionate about protecting the weak. She is also awkward and rigid in her work. One day, due to unforeseen circumstances, Mayuzumi Machiko begins to work at Komikado Kensuke's law office. The two attorneys constantly clash, but in the courtroom they cooperate to fight as one.

title: ctrl+alt+del
body:
Ctrl+Alt+Del (CAD) is a gaming-related webcomic and animated series written and created by Tim Buckley. The name of the comic refers to the Windows command Control-Alt-Delete. Premiering on October 23, 2002, the comic's focus has gradually shifted away from single strip gags towards longer story arcs and greater continuity through the use of video game references. Ctrl+Alt+Del currently is updated every Monday, Wednesday and Friday.

Known for creating the [[loss_(meme)|Loss]] comic strip.

title: white_names_spoiled_past
body:
Lit. "Eastern White Dust Record", also known as [i]Touhou Hakujinki[/i]

An [[original]] [[Touhou]] fangame developed by many of the same people who developed [[The Last Comer]], [[Mystical Power Plant]], and [[Riverbed Soul Saver]]. The full game was released on January 24th, 2015.

It is notable for having a 'mystery novel'-type plot, with one of the main goals is to figure out who the true culprit of the incident is. Also notable is that the main character designer is NRT, who has created various hypothetical official characters (including [[Sashiromiya Sasha]]).

h5.Playable Characters

* [[Hakurei Reimu]] with [[Shourokuzan Tokubi]]
* [[Kirisame Marisa]] with [[Shiragiku Kayano Linne]]
* [[Kochiya Sanae]] with [[Okuchiri Minayu]]

h5.Enemies

[b]Stage 1 Mid-boss:[/b] [[Ikushima Setsujou]]

title: kinomoto_sakura_(water_drop)
body:
A costume that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in [[cardcaptor sakura clear card arc|Clear Card Arc]], specifically in episode 9. Take care not to confuse this with either the [[kinomoto sakura (water fairy)|Water Fairy costume]] or the [[kinomoto sakura (fluffy sheep)|Fluffy Sheep costume]]s from the 90s anime.

She wears a [[blue hat|blue]] [[jester cap]], a [[blue dress|blue]] jester-themed dress over a [[blue skirt]], [[blue gloves|blue]] [[elbow gloves]], and [[blue thighhighs|blue]] [[thigh boots]].

title: kinomoto_sakura_(sakura_prince)
body:
A costume that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in the 90s anime, specifically in episode 42 when she partakes in a school play, and likewise captures the [[Light (clow card)|]] and [[Dark (clow card)|]] Cards. [[Li Syaoran]] humorously wears a [[li syaoran (princess costume)|princess costume]] to complement Sakura's prince outfit.

She wears a [[blue hat]] with white plumed feathers, a [[blue jacket]], a [[red neckerchief]], a [[white cape]]. puffy [[red shorts]], and [[black thighhighs|black]] [[thigh boots]].

title: kinomoto_sakura_(shopgirl:_mint)
body:
A [[official alternate costume|costume]] that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in the 90s anime, specifically during the ending credits song for the third season, titled [i]Fruits Candy[/i]. [[Daidouji Tomoyo]] likewise has a costume of her own called [[daidouji tomoyo (chef: tomoyo)|Chef: Tomoyo]].

Sakura's outfit consists of a striped [[green bowtie]], a [[green vest]] over a [[striped shirt]], a [[white skirt]], [[green shorts]], [[green thighhighs]], and [[green footwear|green]] [[slippers]].

title: kinomoto_sakura_(fluffy_sheep)
body:
A costume that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in the 90s anime, specifically in episode 52 when she changes the [[Erase (clow card)|]] [[Clow Card]] into a [[Sakura Card]]. Although modeled after a jester, this outfit is given the name [b]Fluffy Sheep[/b] to differentiate it from her episode 3 [[kinomoto sakura (water fairy)|Water Fairy costume]], and also because in episode 52, Sakura is trapped in a hole and thousands of toy sheep are falling on top of her. Take care not to confuse with either the Water Fairy costume or the [[kinomoto sakura (water drop)|Water Drop costume]] from [[cardcaptor sakura clear card arc|Clear Card Arc]].

She wears a [[blue hat|blue]] two-pointed [[jester cap]], a [[blue cape]] over [[yellow shorts]], [[yellow gloves]], [[white pantyhose]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[pointed footwear|pointed shoes]].

title: kinomoto_sakura_(water_fairy)
body:
A costume that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in the 90s anime, specifically in episode 3 when she captures the [[Watery (clow card)|]] Card. Be sure not to confuse this outfit for her [[kinomoto sakura (fluffy sheep)|Fluffy Sheep costume]] from episode 52, or her [[kinomoto sakura (water drop)|Water Drop costume]] from [[cardcaptor sakura clear card arc|Clear Card Arc]].

She wears a [[blue hat|blue]] [[jester cap]], a [[white dress|white]] jester-themed dress over a [[blue leotard]], [[blue gloves|blue]] [[elbow gloves]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[pointed footwear|pointed shoes]].

title: kinomoto_sakura_(princess_costume)
body:
A costume that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in the 90s anime, specifically in the second movie when [[Daidouji Tomoyo]] designs it for a school play. [[Li Syaoran]] wears a [[li syaoran (prince costume)|prince-themed costume]] to complement Sakura's princess outfit. Take care not to confuse this outfit with her [[kinomoto sakura (astral sakura)|Astral Sakura dress]], which are very similar in design and coloration.

She wears a dress that is either depicted [[white dress|white]] or light [[pink dress|pink]], a [[red choker|red]] [[star choker]], [[red ribbon]]s around her legs, a frilled thighlet on her left leg, and [[red footwear|red]] [[shoes]].

title: li_syaoran_(prince_costume)
body: An outfit that [[Li Syaoran]] wears in illustrations to accompany [[kinomoto sakura|Sakura]]'s [[kinomoto sakura (princess costume)|princess costume]].

title: li_syaoran_(princess_costume)
body: An outfit that [[Li Syaoran]] wears in a humorous episode involving a play, with [[kinomoto sakura|Sakura]] playing as the [[kinomoto sakura (sakura prince)|prince]]. Syaoran wears a pink dress and a long blonde wig that doesn't cover his brown bangs.

title: li_syaoran_(battle_costume)
body: The green Chinese clothes that [[Li Syaoran]] wears when combatting Clow Cards or helping [[kinomoto sakura|Sakura]] on her missions. Unlike Sakura's numerous battle costumes that are more playful and thematic, Syaoran wears this one for the majority of the series, and they're said to be ceremonial garments passed down through his family.

title: kinomoto_sakura_(pink_star_angel_costume)
body:
A costume that [[Kinomoto Sakura]] wears in the 90s anime, specifically in the second movie when she transforms the [[Nothing (clow card)|]] Card into the [[Hope (clow card)|]] Card. [[Li Syaoran]] has a complementary [[li syaoran (green star angel costume)|green-colored costume]] to go with Sakura's pink-themed outfit.

She wears a [[pink hat]] with a wing ornament on the front, a [[double-breasted]] [[pink shirt]], [[pink gloves|pink]] [[elbow gloves]], a [[pink skirt]] over [[pink shorts]], and [[pink footwear|pink]] [[shoes]].

title: li_syaoran_(green_star_angel_costume)
body: A costume for [[Li Syaoran]] that matches [[kinomoto sakura|Sakura]]'s [[kinomoto sakura (pink star angel costume)|Pink Star Angel Costume]], except that Syaoran's is colored green and has pants and hand gloves. The name [b]Green Star Angel Costume[/b] is fanmade to accompany Sakura's outfit.

title: rush_hour
body:
[b]Rush Hour[/b] is Action Comedy Buddy Cop movie series staring [[Jackie Chan]] and Chris Tucker as Hong Kong Chief Inspector Lee and Los Angeles Police Detective James Carter respectively, a pair of police detectives who go on a series of misadventures fighting corrupt crime figures throughout Hong Kong and Los Angeles. The films incorporate elements of martial arts, humor involving fish out of water situations and East-West culture shock between the two lead characters.

The movies inspired a TV adaptation that aired on CBS in 2016 but was cancelled after one season. Currently, a fourth Rush Hour movie is in the works.

As of 2025 there are currently three Rush Hour movies:

* Rush Hour (1998) 
* Rush Hour 2 (2001)
* Rush Hour 3 (2006)

title: tulip_hat
body:
Similar in appearance to a [[bucket hat]] or [[cloche hat]], the tulip hat typically has no defined brim, nor a ribbon/belt to create the appearance of one, and often has ribbing or panels dividing the hat into vertical sections more reminiscent of the namesake tulip. It can be further embellished with elements that make it look more like an upside down flower, or by rounding the panels to give it a wavy brim.

h4. Examples

title: howto:bluesky
body:
Bluesky is a website that serves as a secondary source to Danbooru.

h4. Artist entries

To create or edit an artist entry, click the '?' next to the artist tag in the tag list. In the artist entry, add:

h6. Other Names

* The artist's display name, located beneath the header.
* The artist's Bluesky handle, without the trailing ".bsky.social".
* Any other account names or nicknames on other sites the artist lists in their profile.

h6. URLs

* The Bluesky profile URL: [code]https://bsky.app/profile/danboorubot.bsky.social[/code]
** You may update the URL if the artist has changed their handle on Bluesky.
** Leave the old URL, but prepend it with a "-".
* The Bluesky DID URL: [code]https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:nb4xwxlztihu5m2c7kyf4kw8[/code]
** The benefit of having this link is that it won't change
* URLs of any other websites the artist lists in their Bluesky profile.

[expand=Bookmarklet to show DID]
[code]javascript:void(()=>prompt("bsky URL",`https://bsky.app/profile/${document.querySelector('meta[content^="did:"]').content}`))()[/code][/expand]

h4. Image quality
As of the time of writing (May 2025), images on Bluesky are constrained to at most 2000 pixels on either dimension, any larger images are squished down to fit this limit. This makes it a sub-optimal source for large images when sources with a looser image size limit are available.

h4. See also

* [[md5 mismatch]]

title: rogue
body:
An ambiguous tag. 

h6. Rogue may refer to:

* A common character class in many [[tag group:role-playing games|role-playing games]], also known as a thief. Traditionally, they have the ability to pick locks, disable traps, and perform stealth maneuvers, but now often just refers to classes that rely on speed and evasion rather than defense or health, and a high number of hits rather than raw damage. They're often seen using [[dagger]]s, [[dual wielding]], and wearing [[hood|hoods]]. Examples include:
** [[Rogue (Ragnarok Online)]]
** [[Rogue (Warcraft)]]

* [[Rogue (X-men)]], a [[Marvel]] character.
* [[Rogue (Nuclear Throne)]], a [[Nuclear Throne]] character.

Not to be confused with [[Rouge the Bat]] from the [i][[Sonic (series)|Sonic]][/i] series.

title: howto:deviantart
body:
[[deviantart|DeviantArt]] is a website where most Western artists upload their work. It serves as another major source of images on Danbooru.

This page will describe how to upload from DeviantArt, in addition to how to handle new artist entries in the case an entry doesn't already exist for the artist you're uploading a work from.

h4. Uploading

Here's the ideal procedure when uploading a DeviantArt artist:

[b]1.[/b] Upload with the "danbooru bookmarklet":[/static/bookmarklet], or paste in the URL of the work you wish to upload in the upload page. This way, you don't have to upload the image from your computer and risk it being an [[image sample]]. For more technical details, you may expand the following:

[expand]
Upload from DeviantArt (not from your computer) with the [b]full image URL[/b] if possible. On the right side, there should be a link to the URL labeled "Download". If it's not there, zoom into the picture as much as possible and copy the image URL from there. 

Since Danbooru supports direct linking to the image URL, the source URL should look like one of the following:

[quote]
http[i]:[/i]//[b]orig[/b]10.deviantart.net/b1f7/f/2015/169/1/b/1b095k69ceedwac54177e18132g8a084-d8xbdx0.jpg
http[i]:[/i]//[b]orig[/b]09.deviantart.net/cb07/f/2015/172/f/1/k_by_sampleartist-d4kso7f.png
[/quote]

Or if the original source URL cannot be accessed for whatever reason (that is, when the download button will not be present):

[quote]
http[i]:[/i]//[b]img[/b]14.deviantart.net/2d53/i/2015/156/a/c/___sample_work___by_sampleartist-d8w7vhm.jpg
[/quote]

DeviantArt has reduced-size versions of its images known as [[deviantart sample]]s, none of which should be uploaded here. Your source URL should not look like these:

[quote]
http[i]:[/i]//[b]pre[/b]03.deviantart.net/31ed/th/pre/f/2015/172/f/1/k_by_sampleartist-djy6akj.png
http[i]:[/i]//[b]pre[/b]07.deviantart.net/1a1f/th/pre/f/2015/169/1/b/1b095069ceedfacfdty177e18132b8a084-d4dudx0.jpg
[/quote]

[/expand]

[b]2.[/b] Use the artist tag detected by Danbooru under Related Tags, if there is one. If not, follow the rest of this howto to create a new artist tag.

* Do a [[help:cheatsheet|source:*username* search]] for the DeviantArt username. The username is usually found in image source URL. For example, search {{source:*shirononochiko*}} if the source URL is http[i]:[/i]//orig00.deviantart.net/e1d7/f/2013/096/7/2/nonexistent_work_by_[b]shirononochiko[/b]-gj83sbo8.png.
* If you find any posts and they already have an artist tag, use that tag. You will need to update the artist entry so that Danbooru will automatically detect the artist tag for future uploads. See [b]Artist Entries[/b] to learn how to do this.
* If this search didn't turn up any posts, or you find posts but they don't have an artist tag, then you will have to make a new artist tag yourself. Edit the post and add [b]artist:artist_name[/b] to the tags. See [b]Artist Naming[/b] for advice on choosing a name. After making a new artist tag, you will also have to create an artist entry. See [b]Artist Entries[/b] to learn how to do this.

h4. Artist Naming

The first choice is to use the artist's full real name, if you can find it. On the main profile under the artist's username, there should be a section that shows the artist's real name, gender, and location. The name should have both a first and a last name. If it's in non-English letters, follow Danbooru's [[howto:romanize|romanization guidelines]]. Otherwise, check any personal websites or blogs they may list in their DeviantArt profile. See [[help:artists]] for advice on finding the artist's name on their website.

The second choice is their DeviantArt username.

h4. Artist Entries

After creating a new artist tag, click the '?' next to the artist tag in the tag list to create a new artist entry. In the artist entry add:

h6. Other Names
* Any other account names, Twitter handles, or nicknames on other sites the artist lists in their profile.

h6. URLs
* The DeviantArt profile URL: [b]h[/b][b]ttp://sampleartist.deviantart.com/[/b]
* URLs of any other websites the artist lists in their DeviantArt profile.

h4. See also

* [[deviantart sample]]
* [[bad deviantart id]]
* [[md5 mismatch]]

title: uchi_no_otouto_maji_de_dekain_dakedo_mi_ni_konai
body:
A boy named Nao, a young preteen, is caught masturbating in the bathroom by his older teen sister Chiaki after having broken his beloved sex toy, Sakura-chan. Far from disturbed, Chiaki is surprised by the size of her younger brother's penis and takes a photo of it to share with her friends, urging them to come over to see his "Cockzilla."

The very next day, two girls named Nagisa and Yukiko arrive at Chiaki's house to look at Nao's Cockzilla. Shamelessly, Chiaki exposes her brother's body before her friends' astonished eyes while they start discussing his size. With the intention of knowing its true caliber, they engage in stimulating it beyond its limits.

title: a_shuai_on_line
body: 阿衰on line, aka a shuai on line, is a popular Chinese bcomic and animated series centered around the misadventures of its titular character, A Shuai (阿衰), a cheeky, unlucky, and socially awkward middle school student. Known for its slapstick humor and relatable school-life scenarios, the series humorously explores themes like friendship, teenage struggles, and the chaos of growing up. Originally a long-running comic by cartoonist Mao Xiaole (猫小乐), it gained a massive following in China and was adapted into an animated series, amplifying its appeal through exaggerated gags and A Shuai’s endearing underdog persona.

title: shin_megami_tensei
body:
[b]Shin Megami Tensei[/b] (真・女神転生, lit. "True Goddess Reincarnation") is a series of RPGs developed and published by [[Atlus]]. It is originally based on the [[Digital Devil Story]] series of books, and the [[Famicom]] games developed by Atlus ([[Megami Tensei (Famicom)]] and [[Megami Tensei II]]).

The games are usually standalone stories taking place in post-apocalyptic worlds with recurring themes of philosophy, religion, occultism, and [[science fiction]]. 

Key elements of the gameplay include: (1) player-driven choices to place the protagonist in an ideological "alignment" (usually Law/Chaos/Neutral); (2) the recruitment and use of demons/creatures/deities/historical figures from various mythologies and folklore. Colloquially by fans and in-game they are all usually just referred to collectively as demons. Use the general [[Demon (Megami Tensei)]] tag whenever they are featured in posts.

For Danbooru purposes this tag is exclusively used for the set of mainline games and [[Megami Tensei]] is used for the overarching franchise. See that wiki for a list of spinoff series.

h4. Mainline Games

* [[Shin Megami Tensei I]] (1992, [[Super Famicom]])
* [[Shin Megami Tensei II]] (1994, Super Famicom)
* [[Shin Megami Tensei: if...]] (1994, Super Famicom)
* [[Shin Megami Tensei NINE]] (2002, [[Xbox (original)|]])
* [[Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne]] (2003, [[Playstation 2]])
* [[Shin Megami Tensei IMAGINE]] (2007, PC)
* [[Shin Megami Tensei: Strange Journey]] (2009, [[Nintendo DS]])
* [[Shin Megami Tensei IV]] (2013, [[Nintendo 3DS]])
* [[Shin Megami Tensei IV Final]] (2016, Nintendo 3DS)
* [[Shin Megami Tensei: Liberation Dx2]] (2018, Mobile gacha)
* [[Shin Megami Tensei V]] (2021, [[Nintendo Switch]])
* [[Shin Megami Tensei V: Vengeance]] (2024, Nintendo Switch)

h4. See also

* [[List of Shin Megami Tensei demons]]

title: sasaki_to_p-chan
body:
Sasaki to P-chan (EN Title: Sasaki and Peeps) is a Japanese light novel series written by Buncololi and illustrated by [[Kantoku]]. It was originally published as a web novel. A TV anime adaptation was announced in the works in July 2022.

The series is a fantasy comedy revolving around the titular [[Sasaki (sasaki to p-chan)|]], a 39-year-old salary man, who one day purchases a Java sparrow for companionship. Upon bringing the bird home to his six-tatami mat sized apartment, the bird talks to him and identifies himself as Piercarlo the Starsage from another world. Thus begins Sasaki's hectic life of traveling to and from a fantasy world, getting pulled in to a secret conflict involving psychics, encountering dangerous magical girls, and getting caught in the middle of a death game battle between angels and demons.

h4. Characters

h5. Main Characters

* [[Sasaki (sasaki to p-chan)|]]

title: million_dreams_(idolmaster)
body:
Million Dreams is a [[LUXURY (idolmaster)|]] costume that primarily appears in the Million Live! brand. It was introduced in [[iDOLMaSTER Million Live!|THE iDOLM@STER Million Live!]]. It has made subsequent appearances in the following 2nd Vision games, and the costume is used in [[iDOLMaSTER Million Live! Theater Days|THE iDOLM@STER Million Live! Theater Days]] as the costume for N+ card illustrations.
These are [[Pink Diamond 765 (idolmaster)|]] color changes.

Although it is mainly associated with Million Live!, Million Dreams has appeared in the main games as well. The first time it appeared in a home console game was the [[PlayStation 3]] version of [[idolmaster 2|THE iDOLM@STER 2]], where it can be obtained from the game's eighteenth DLC catalog. It also appeared in [[idolmaster one for all|THE iDOLM@STER ONE FOR ALL]], where it is a base game costume that can be purchased in-game for 96,000 money at Lucky Rabbit.

h4. External links

* "project-imas wiki":https://project-imas.wiki/Million_Dreams

It consists of a [[white shirt|white]] [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[collared shirt]] underneath a [[blue vest]], a [[blue cape]], [[white gloves]], [[black pants]] with a [[thigh strap]] on his left leg, [[black boots|black]] [[fold-over boots|fold-over]] [[knee boots]] and a [[white ascot]] draped from his [[necklace]]. title: sheeeh!
body:
A peculiar and infamous pose done by [[Iyami]] in the manga [i][[Osomatsu-kun]][/i]. It is accomplished by stretching out the forearm and bending a leg upwards while shouting the titular phrase (a shoe falling off is optional). In the West, the pose is most famous for its use in Showa era [[Godzilla (series)|]] after first appearing in [i]Invasion of Astro-Monster[/i].

* !post #2184244

title: gilzaren_iii_(1st_costume)
body:
The default costume of [[Nijisanji]]'s [[Gilzaren III]]. 

It consists of an [[white ascot]] draped from his [[necklace]], an [[open jacket|open]] [[black jacket]], [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]], [[white gloves]], [[black pants]], a [[red cape|red]] and [[black cape|black]] [[two-sided cape|two-sided]] [[high collar]]ed [[cape]] and a pair of [[black boots|black]] [[fold-over boots|fold-over]] [[knee boots]]. He wears a [[thigh strap]] on his left leg and has two [[crossed belts|crossed]] [[black belt]]s.

title: vikala_(granblue_fantasy)
body:
2020 [[Chinese Zodiac]] character in [[Granblue Fantasy]].

Guardian of the North and one of the Twelve Divine Generals, she is the zodiac representative for the [[year of the rat|Rat]]. Her "yang" side is determined to bring hope, dreams, and wonderment to the world. Her "yin" side wants nothing more than to hide away from it. Caught between two extremes, the divine rat pins her hopes on the wide-open skies and chooses to trust in her new friends.

h4.Official alternate costumes

* [[vikala_(blooming_summer_wallflower)_(granblue_fantasy)|Blooming Summer Wallflower]]

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] in a [[ponytail]] and [[orange eyes|orange]] [[empty eyes]]. She wears a [[short dress|short]] red and white dress, black thighhighs, [[brown footwear|brown]] [[lace-up boots]], and moderate armour. In the summer beach festival event she wears an elaborate white, black, and orange themed outfit being consisting of a bikini, criss-cross black thighhighs adorned with bows, and a [[hibiscus]] in her hair.

title: bea_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Bea[/b], known as [b]Saitou[/b] (サイトウ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon swsh|Sword and Shield]][/i].

This Gym Leader is a karate prodigy from Galar who is highly disciplined and trains daily. She also loves sweets, but she likes to keep that a secret [tn](official bio)[/tn].

She has [[grey eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] with [[hair between eyes|long bangs]]. She wears a [[black hairband|black]] [[bow hairband|hairband]], a [[black bodysuit|bodysuit]] [[bodysuit under clothes|under]] a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeve]] [[print shirt|shirt]] and [[side slit shorts|side slit]] [[print shorts|shorts]], a [[dynamax band|wristband]], [[single glove|a]] [[partially fingerless gloves|glove]], [[knee pads]], and is [[barefoot]].

title: shingeki_no_kyojin
body:
[b]Shingeki no Kyojin[/b] (also known as [b]Attack on Titan[/b]) is a manga by [[Isayama Hajime]].

In an alternative past, humanity has been attacked by monstrous giants called [[titan_(shingeki_no_kyojin)|Titans]]. What remains of it has barricaded itself behind a 3-walled fortress-country, and any attempt at war against the Titans has ended with disastrous results. The Titans, however, were unable to breach the walls, and so humanity has lived in safety for a century. One day, 2 unusual Titans appear out of nowhere and destroy the gate of the outer wall. In the ensuing massacre, Eren Yeager sees his mother devoured before his eyes. Swearing to eradicate all Titans, he enlists in the army alongside his adopted sister Mikasa Ackerman and friend Armin Arlert.

Nominated for the 4th Manga Taishou Awards (2011) and winner of the 35th annual Kodansha Manga Award for Best Shounen, Nominated for the 16th Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize (2012).

[[Socks]] that are at "ankle length".

Despite the name, the tag refers to socks that are slightly above the ankles, not the extremely short ones that stop exactly at or below the ankles. They end before the shins, if they go over the shins, they become [[kneehighs]].

Not to be confused with [[bootie]]s, a sock-like garment that is also ankle length.

title: holy_samba_night
body:
[b]Christmas 2018: Holy Samba Night ~The Snowy Ruins and the Girl Knight~[/b]
[quote]Tis the season of Santa once more in Chaldea. This year, the previous Santa has selected a certain goddess to inherit the power of Santa Claus.

"Leave it to me! I'm very good at this sort of thing, yes!"

And as she tackled her Santa duties in a surprisingly normal way, it seemed this year's Christmas was going to go off without a hitch... That is, until Chaldea detected a new Singularity in Mexico. Master and company head there to investigate, and find themselves in a snow-covered city filled with the sounds of winter rejoicing.

"I had my suspicions, but..."
"This isn't Santa! This is samba!"

A new kind of miracle descends upon the city where masked fighters assembl! The starting bell of this thrilling carnival of the holy night rings...now![/quote]

A limited time [[Christmas]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on December 12, 2018 and on the NA server on December 13, 2020. [[Quetzalcoatl (Samba/Santa) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: bremerton_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the US Navy heavy cruiser USS [i]Bremerton[/i] (CA-130). Character design by [[Katsudansou]].

She has [[pink eyes]] and [[pink hair]] with [[grey hair|grey]] [[streaked hair]], tied in [[twintails]] with [[hair intakes]]. Other minor details include a [[mole under eye|mole under her right eye]] and [[mole on breast|right breast]]. Her most notable features, however, are her very [[large breasts]], and [[ear piercing|ear]] and [[navel piercing]]s. This, combined with her overall design, caused her to be associated with [[gyaru]] stereotypes.

Her outfit consists of a [[crop top]] (usually depicted as [[crop top overhang]]) and [[black shorts|black]] [[short shorts]] worn over a [[pink bikini|pink]] [[bikini]], a [[lifebuoy ornament|lifebuoy]]-shaped [[black choker]], black [[thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[ankle boots]]. Her "combat outfit" also features an [[blue coat|indigo coat]] bearing her designation and a [[red-tinted eyewear|red]] [[aviator sunglasses]].
